resources.description:
Search of assistants is available by name and by MEPs. 
		 
The list of assistants distinguishes: 

1.	 Accredited assistants:  based in one of the European Parliament's three places of work (Brussels, Luxembourg or Strasbourg) with a contract of employment under European law concluded directly with Parliament. 

2.	Local assistants:  based in one of the EU Member States and has a contract of employment governed by private law that is concluded with the Member and is subject to national law.
resources.name: MEP's assistants

description:
The dataset contains information about each of the 751 Members of the European Parliament (MEPs) elected in 2014: the country they represent, the political group and the national political party. 

In addition, you will also find information on: 
	  
-           incoming and outgoing MEPs,

-           MEPs' assistants, 

-           the full list of MEPs in each parliamentary term, since 1979, and

-           links to search pages where information can be visualised by several criteria.   

Further information on MEPs, including their CV, parliamentary activity, assistants and contact details is available on the website of the European Parliament: http://www.europarl.europa.eu/meps/en/crosstable.html
title: Members of the European Parliament (MEPs)
name: members-of-the-european-parliament
contact_address: Bât. Altiero Spinelli, 60 rue Wiertz / Wiertzstraat 60, B-1047 - Bruxelles/Brussels, Belgium,
